snippet.textDisplay: yeah I had to pull out a tooth as an adult as well (never had any such issues as a kid), but for different reasons, and the way my dentist explained what she and her nurse were gunna do, modern dentist don't just pull teeth straight out: they basically use a tiny chisel to wedge the tooth and twirl it until the "strings" that connects the roots snap from tension and THEN they can just pluck the tooth out like nothing. The needle giving your jaw a shot of numbing painkillers "hurt" more than the actual procedure: you can feel the tension in the root-strings snapping and the now loose tooth being removed from your gum, but it doesn't actually hurt. Gotta love modern medical technology: I have lost count how many times my parents have needed to repair their teeth and fillings because when they grew up dentists basically cut off the top and hollowed out entire teeth just to fill tiny holes, but if I look in a mirror I can't even see the spot my dentist filled my hole, it just looks like a normal, healthy tooth, despite the black hole itself being very visible to the naked eye before that.
